oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Alfalfa for soil conservation program
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: C.W. Wilcher is shown in alfalfa field seeded as a part of planned soil and water conservation program on his farm. Land was treated in accordance with recommendations based on soil test before seeding. Crop is ten days before ready to cut. Located two miles south of Woodbury.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
